(582, 14520, 1, 12, 50, 0, 0, 0, 50, 'Valid for all performances', '2022-06-20', '21:00:00', 1, 'The Deathless Woman, Directed by Roz Mortimer, 2019, 89 mins / 20 June 9pm<br>  The Deathless Woman is a ghost story for the 21st Century. This urgent and magical hybrid documentary fluidly interweaves fantastical re-imaginings of buried secrets with a ghostly narration and direct to camera testimony from survivors and witnesses of historic and contemporary crimes against the Roma in Poland and Hungary. A Roma woman buried alive in a forest in Poland during WWII returns to haunt us, uncovering a history of atrocities against the Roma in Europe. She is the Deathless Woman. Motivated by rage, she rises from her grave to draw our attention to the persecution of the Roma people from the 1940s to the neo-Nazi hate crimes of the present day.<br>  THAMESMEAD TEXAS presents: <br> Thamesmead Texas have produced a special screening programme marking Gypsy, Romany, Traveller communities to coincide with GRT month. Screening weekend from The Thamesmead Travelling Cinema, Lakeside Centre, 19-20 June as part of National Lottery Cinema Weekend 2021. <br>  The Thamesmead Texas bar is open from 7pm. Last admission at 8:45pm for a 9pm screening. Present your booking confirmation at the box office to redeem your free cinema ticket(s). Look forward to seeing you there! Vanessa and Liam<br> The Thamesmead Travelling Cinema is currently based at the Lakeside Centre, 2 Bazalgette Way, Thamesmead, SE2 9AN. The Lakeside Centre is a gated building, which can be accessed from the street located between The Link and the lakeside public parking lot. Thamesmead can be accessed via Abbey Wood train station - is two stops East of Woolwich and 30 minutes East of London Bridge. Walking distance from Abbey Wood train station to Lakeside Centre is 15 minutes. If driving, parking is available for free.  Closest bus stop: Newacres Library, bus route 177, 301, 401. Please ensure you factor travel/ walk time into your journey planning.', '0.00', '0.00', 3600, 12, 1000, 240, 240, '2001-01-01 00:00:00', 0, 'The Deathless Woman, Directed by Roz Mortimer, 2019, 89 mins', 'Europe/London', 1, ''),
(584, 14520, 1, 14, 50, 0, 0, 0, 50, 'Valid for all performances', '2022-06-19', '21:00:00', 1, 'Into the West, Directed by Mike Newell, 1992, 97 mins/ 19 June 9 pm<br>  Into the West is a 1992 Irish magical realist film about Irish Travellers written by Jim Sheridan and directed by Mike Newell, starring Gabriel Byrne and Ellen Barkin.<br>  THAMESMEAD TEXAS presents: <br> Thamesmead Texas have produced a special screening programme marking Gypsy, Romany, Traveller communities to coincide with GRT month. Screening weekend from The Thamesmead Travelling Cinema, Lakeside Centre, 19-20 June as part of National Lottery Cinema Weekend 2021.  <br> The Thamesmead Texas bar is open from 7pm. Last admission at 8:45pm for a 9pm screening. Present your booking confirmation at the box office to redeem your free cinema ticket(s). Look forward to seeing you there! Vanessa and Liam<br> The Thamesmead Travelling Cinema is currently based at the Lakeside Centre, 2 Bazalgette Way, Thamesmead, SE2 9AN. The Lakeside Centre is a gated building, which can be accessed from the street located between The Link and the lakeside public parking lot. Thamesmead can be accessed via Abbey Wood train station - is two stops East of Woolwich and 30 minutes East of London Bridge. Walking distance from Abbey Wood train station to Lakeside Centre is 15 minutes. If driving, parking is available for free.  Closest bus stop: Newacres Library, bus route 177, 301, 401. Please ensure you factor travel/ walk time into your journey planning.', '0.00', '0.00', 3600, 12, 1000, 240, 240, '2001-01-01 00:00:00', 0, 'Into the West, Directed by Mike Newell, 1992, 97 mins/ 19 June', 'Europe/London', 1, ''),
